---
description: Stylesheet ownership map for split CSS architecture.
globs:
  - "app/styles/**/*.css"
  - "app/globals.css"
alwaysApply: true
---

Use this ownership map:

- `app/styles/tokens.css`: variables, theme tokens, global measurements
- `app/styles/shell.css`: app shell, header, shared rail/container scaffolding
- `app/styles/dashboard.css`: queue rows, left rail blocks, job detail + prep shared surfaces
- `app/styles/settings.css`: settings-page layout contracts and elevated controls
- `app/styles/forms.css`: shared fields, uploads, disclosures, form states
- `app/styles/operators.css`: operators/account screen only
- `app/styles/responsive.css`: breakpoint-only overrides

Rules:
- Do not move layout logic into random component-level selectors when a shared file already owns it.
- `app/globals.css` is import order only, not the place for surface-specific styling.
- Keep zero visual diff when reorganizing CSS ownership.
